# ğŸ Bug report

### Affected Package
compiler

### Description

When using destructuring in a module-factory, the AoT-build seems to create a bundle with the wrong value.
The following code provides ` {prop1:{prop1:"prop1",prop2:"prop2"},prop2:undefined} ` instead of `{prop1:"prop1",prop2:"prop2"}`:
```
public static forRoot(
    { prop1 = "prop1", prop2 = "prop2" }: Partial<Bug>
): ModuleWithProviders
{
    return {
        ngModule: BugModule,
        providers: [
            { provide: BUG_TOKEN, useValue: { prop1, prop2 } },
        ]
    };
}
```
I inspected the generated `main.*.js` and it seems like the AoT-build inlines the value, but it is not calculated correctly.

## ğŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction

A minimal reproduction can be found [here](https://github.com/Springrbua/aot-destructuring-bug).
Steps to reproduce:

1. Execute `ng build --prod`
2. Open `main.*.js` and search for `prop1`. You will find the following Object:  
    `{prop1:{prop1:"First Property",prop2:"Second Property"},prop2:void 0}`
3. Open `bug.module.ts` and enable the workaround by removing the comment form line 9 and line 16 and putting line 8 and line 15 in comment instead.
4. Run `ng build --prod` again.
5. Open the new `main.*.js` and search for `prop1` again. Now the Object has the correct value  
    `{prop1:"First Property",prop2:"Second Property"}`

